Date: 0/0/1966
Source: Boss's Story, The
Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 190
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Slew</i>: To slew sheep is to turn them in a different direction to that in which they are going. If sheep are sidling round a face and they have to be turned downhill a dog is run out and above them to `slew' them down.
Notes:

