Quote: <i>Slew:</i> A huntaway should be able to cast to the side on command and slew in the desired direction.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1971
Source: Ten Thousand Dogs
Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: A mob of those wethers, slewed out of a high basin, would disappear down a spur in a cloud of dust ... <i>Ibid.</i> 169  <i>Slew</i>: To turn or change the direction in which sheep are travelling. To top-side slew is to turn or hunt them downhill. Slewing is done mainly with huntaways and in one of the huntaways events at our trials - Class III - the sheep are hunted on a zig-zag course. This is often called a slew.
